                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                text="&lt;p>AbbVie grant requests originating from the United States and Puerto Rico are managed by a centralized grant department and more information is available at grants.abbvie.com.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>AbbVie discloses donations and grants made by the company because we are committed to sharing our commitment to promote health education and charitable causes that ultimately benefit patients.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>The list of AbbVie’s grants and contributions are provided in the annual report below. AbbVie’s report reflects&amp;nbsp;educational grants, patient support, charitable donations, as well as fellowships and scholarships. The report includes individual direct payments of more than $200 from AbbVie’s US and Puerto Rico businesses.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>Annual Report&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;a href=&quot;/content/dam/abbvie-com2/pdfs/grants/2024-AbbVie-Grants-and-Contributions-Report.pdf&quot;>2024&lt;/a>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;i>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;AbbVie officially became a company January 1, 2013. In May 2020, AbbVie completed the acquisition of Allergan and began operating as a combined company.&lt;/i>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
